SIMPLE: hive
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hive
<hw>Hive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>hive</ets>,
<ets>huve</ets>, AS. <ets>h<?/fe</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A box,
basket, or other structure, for the reception and habitation of a swarm
of honeybees.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The bees of one hive; a swarm of bees.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A place swarming with busy occupants; a
crowd.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>hive</qex> of Roman liars.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hive bee</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
honeybee.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hive
<hw>Hive</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hived</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hiving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To collect into a
hive; to place in, or cause to enter, a hive; <as>as, to <ex>hive</ex> a
swarm of bees</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To store up in a hive, as honey; hence, to gather
and accumulate for future need; to lay up in store.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Hiving</qex> wisdom with each studious year.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hive
<hw>Hive</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To take shelter or lodgings
together; to reside in a collective body.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hiveless</ent>⟦br⟧
